---
import ContentSection from '../ContentSection.astro';
import Flowchart from '../Flowchart.astro';

const artMovements = {
  nodes: [
    { id: "A", label: "Photography Movements" },
    { id: "B", label: "Pictorialism" },
    { id: "C", label: "Straight Photography" },
    { id: "D", label: "Documentary" },
    { id: "E", label: "Modern Art" },
    { id: "F", label: "Contemporary" }
  ],
  connections: [
    { from: "A", to: "B" },
    { from: "B", to: "C" },
    { from: "C", to: "D" },
    { from: "D", to: "E" },
    { from: "E", to: "F" }
  ]
};
---

<ContentSection title="Photography as Art">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">The Artistic Journey</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Photography's recognition as an art form was a gradual process. Initially viewed merely as a mechanical reproduction tool, it evolved through various artistic movements and styles to become a respected medium of creative expression.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Major Artistic Movements</h3>
      <Flowchart data={artMovements} />
      
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Pictorialism (1890s-1910s)</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Emphasized beauty and composition over pure documentation</li>
            <li>Used soft focus and manipulation techniques</li>
            <li>Aimed to emulate painting styles</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Straight Photography (1910s-1930s)</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Focused on sharp, clearly defined images</li>
            <li>Emphasized photography's unique qualities</li>
            <li>Led by photographers like Paul Strand and Edward Weston</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-2">Modern Photography</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Experimental techniques and abstract compositions</li>
            <li>Integration with other art movements</li>
            <li>Focus on form, pattern, and texture</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ContentSection>